rom not that for me someone had to do that joke i'm sorry i was the first one so why prometheus actually we didn't get we asked our devops asking the community and we got recommended not really prometheus was not the first recommendation so i i want to point out that we analyzed it and we decided to use prometheus because of some reasons not because someone told us to use prometheus or recommend to use prometheus and the first thing we like we talked about the labels and at that point we didn't have any monitoring so we didn't know what we wanted to monitor so we didn't know we didn't have a fixed model of metrics at in advance we wanted to have something flexible to decide afterwards if it was correct or not and to evolve so that labels and that flexibility was checked for prometheus uh there's no need for the simplicity wanted to test first like hey let's give it a try uh you don't need to well for example since it was one of the recommendations you need to set up a messaging system robert mq and redis it was like yeah with permits you don't really need anything so it's easy to test uh it offers a possibility of using a dns for service discovery and we already had an internal dns so it was sort of a perfect match idea we can use our internal dns for service discover great and it's easy to install and test and the docker image watch works perfectly and very simple so we gave it a try what we did on the very beginning and please do not be scared i'm gonna explain some things that are really wrong but yeah so the first thing we were using ansible for deployment so it was pretty easy for us to use ansible to create the targets the target list so it was manually fed and every every time you wanted to update it we had you have to rerun ansible and then we finally linked that service discovery with our internal dns which was working fine and at that time we only had the metrics provided by the node exporter like this uh instance app and all the things you can see but we 